Provenance
----------
The wire-protocol server (`src/pgwire_calcite/`) and the vendored codec
(`vendor/buenavista/`) were copied verbatim from the `provisa` codebase
(also (c) 2026 Kenneth Stott, Business Source License 1.1). Per-file copyright
headers and canary identifiers are preserved from the originals. Only the
backend seam (execution + catalog population) has been swapped to target Apache
Calcite instead of Trino; see docs/pgwire-calcite-server-requirements.md (D1).

Vendored components
-------------------
`vendor/buenavista/` — a fork of buenavista (originally Apache-2.0, Josh Wills),
modified by provisa to add binary codecs for DECIMAL, JSON, and array types, and
redistributed here under BSL 1.1 per the provisa fork.

Important
---------
Because this subtree is BSL 1.1, it MUST NOT be contributed upstream to
apache/calcite (which is Apache-2.0) without a separate relicensing by the
copyright holder. The BSL Change Date (2029-01-21) converts it to Apache-2.0.

The per-file NOTICE prohibiting use of this software for training AI/ML models
without explicit written permission applies to every file in this subtree.
